# {{APP_NAME}}

A Next.js 14 (app router) web app with streaming in-browser chat, powered
by [`@mlc-ai/web-llm`](https://github.com/mlc-ai/web-llm) (WebGPU) and
[`@revhappy/activation-sdk`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@revhappy/activation-sdk)
+ [`@revhappy/ui`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@revhappy/ui).

## Prerequisites

- Node 20+.
- A browser with WebGPU enabled (Chrome / Edge 113+, Safari 18+, Firefox
  Nightly with `dom.webgpu.enabled`).

## Get started

```bash
{{PACKAGE_MANAGER}} install
{{PACKAGE_MANAGER}} run dev
```

The first time you open the page, `@mlc-ai/web-llm` will download the
WebLLM model weights into browser storage (IndexedDB). Subsequent loads
pull from cache.

## What's in `src/`

- **`lib/webLlmRuntime.ts`** — an `ActivationRuntime` adapter that wraps
  `@mlc-ai/web-llm`'s `CreateMLCEngine` + streaming chat completions.
  Swap or extend it freely. Default WebLLM model:
  `Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct-q4f32_1-MLC`.
- **`app/layout.tsx`** — Next.js root layout.
- **`app/page.tsx`** — client component. Creates the Machine, wires
  `<MachineProvider>` around the chat screen.
- **`app/ChatScreen.tsx`** — the chat UI. `useMachineModel({ cartridge })`
  picks the cartridge, `useInference(model)` drives streaming, and
  `<InferenceIndicator>` renders status.

## Pick a WebLLM model

Browse the full model list at
<https://github.com/mlc-ai/web-llm/blob/main/src/config.ts> and update
the fallback in `webLlmRuntime.ts` (or thread it through
`ActivationSessionCreateInput.filePath`).

## Why two model ids?

`CARTRIDGE_ID` (e.g. `dev.machine.gemma-3n-e4b-it`) is the cartridge spec
resolved by `@revhappy/activation-sdk`. The WebLLM model id (e.g.
`Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct-q4f32_1-MLC`) is what `@mlc-ai/web-llm` downloads
into the browser. This template uses a hard-coded WebLLM model — wire a
real cartridge resolver if you want the cartridge metadata to drive the
WebLLM pick.

## Next steps

- Replace the placeholder WebLLM model id with one that fits your UX
  budget (smaller = faster first-load, larger = better quality).
- Add streaming fallbacks for non-WebGPU browsers (e.g. a server-side
  route).
- Style the UI to taste — `@revhappy/ui/web` components emit
  `data-machine-ui="<name>"` attributes so you can target them in CSS or
  Tailwind.
